<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>INTERNATIONAL&#174; VT 365 DIESEL ENGINE - ELECTRONICALLY CONTROLLED VARIABLE GEOMETRY TURBOCHARGER (VGT) -
        Operation - Installation
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="12">
        <title>Installation</title>
        <svcsubproc id="S2350201">
            <title>Control Valve</title>
            <figure id="f2350232" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1507.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Lubricating O-rings</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">For reassembly, always replace and lubricate O-rings with clean engine oil. Make sure
                    that O-rings are seated in their correct locations and are not twisted or distorted.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2650204" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1506.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px"
                         scalefitheight="312px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. VGT control valve</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install control valve carefully to prevent twisting or cutting O-rings.</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not use the retaining bolt to draw the control valve into the housing. Push the control
                        valve in by hand to seat securely before installing bracket and bolt.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <figure id="f2350233" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1505.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Control valve retaining bolt</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f2350233">Install control valve bracket and retaining bolt</hotlnk>
                    and tighten bolt to standard torque .
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc id="S2350202">
            <title>Turbocharger Assembly and Components</title>
            <figure id="f2350218" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1516.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Installing turbocharger bracket</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">EGR cooler coolant inlet tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger bracket</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f2350218">Place turbocharger bracket into engine valley</hotlnk>by placing right
                    side of bracket under EGR cooler coolant inlet tube. Then lower left side over bolt holes.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2350220" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1515.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Turbocharger bracket bolts</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install four M8 x 20 mounting bolts to secure turbocharger bracket to crankcase. Tighten
                    bolts to the standard torque .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2350221" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1511.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Turbocharger oil drain tube O-rings</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install two new oil drain tube O-rings and lubricate with clean engine oil. Install
                    drain pipe into the hydraulic pump cover.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2350224" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1514.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 54. Turbocharger alignment dowels and bosses</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Alignment dowel</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Alignment boss</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use alignment dowels to locate turbocharger onto mounting bracket bosses. Lower
                    turbocharger assembly onto mounting bracket and onto oil drain tube.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use three M8 x 30 flange head bolts to secure the turbocharger to its mounting bracket.
                    Coat all bolt threads with antiseize compound and tighten bolts to the special torque .
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2350229" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1502.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 55. Exhaust adapter V-clamp</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten turbocharger exhaust adapter V-clamp to the special torque</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the VGT control valve electrical harness.</para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2350230" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1526.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 56. Turbocharger oil supply tube</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger oil supply tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install turbocharger oil supply tube into oil supply port by pushing in connector until
                    latching mechanism is engaged. Pull up on tube to ensure latching mechanism is engaged. Tube must
                    not pull out of oil supply port.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2350230.5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1535.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 57. Oil inlet hole</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>To prevent engine damage, prelubricate VGT bearings when installing the VGT.</para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Prelubricate the oil inlet hole of the turbocharger assembly with clean engine oil and
                    spin compressor wheel several times to coat bearings with oil. Refill the oil inlet hole up to oil
                    supply tube mounting surface.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2350232.5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1521.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 58. Oil supply tube</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Turbocharger oil supply tube</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Mounting bolts</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position oil supply tube over a new gasket and secure with two M8 x 20 bolts. Tighten to
                    the standard torque . Alternate tightening between both bolts until the proper torque is reached.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f2350235" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figd15/D1522.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="no"/>
                <caption>Figure 59. Securing air inlet duct to turbocharger</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Air inlet duct</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Hose clamp</callout1>
                    <callout1 type="arabic">Breather hose with pitot tube</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Press breather hose assembly into valve cover until it locks into place.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align arrow on duct with feature on turbocharger compressor housing.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Secure air inlet duct to turbocharger by tightening hose clamp to the special torque..
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
